intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of this course students will be able to:
explain and apply the techniques used to create viral user growth in tech companies;
create a growth strategy for a start-up, designed to drive exponential growth.
explain the key metrics involved in driving start-up exponential growth, and how to optimise those metrics;
qualitatively and quantitatively predict the growth performance of a product or start-up based on current growth metrics
analyse and explain why some start-ups grow into very large-scale organisations, while others with similar products fail;
explain how growth teams are configured inside leading start-ups and the development models used by them.
